│   ├─► Understand Landscape → Use Competitive Alternative Mapper
│   ├─► Define Value → Use Differentiated Value Chain Builder
│   ├─► Find Best Customers → Use Target Customer Sharpener
│   └─► Set Context → Use Market Category Selector
│
├─► BUILD A SALES PITCH
│   ├─► Full Pitch Build → Use Sales Pitch Architect
│   ├─► Opening Insight → Use Insight Reverse-Engineer
│   ├─► Mid-Pitch Alignment → Use Perfect World Bridge Builder
│   ├─► Enterprise Deals → Use Champion Ammunition Kit
│   └─► Credibility Layer → Use Proof Stack Assembler
│
├─► FIX A STALLING PIPELINE
│   ├─► Deals Ending in No Decision → Use Buyer Indecision Reducer
│   ├─► Test New Messaging → Use Pitch Testing Protocol
│   └─► Diagnose Root Cause → Use Positioning Diagnostic
│
└─► GO-TO-MARKET EXPANSION
    ├─► Sequential Growth → Use Bowling Pin Strategy Planner
    └─► Category Decision → Use Market Category Selector
```

## Quick Start

### 24-Hour Quickstart
1. Read [genius-patterns.md](references/genius-patterns.md) to internalize "positioning is context-setting, not messaging"
2. Run the [Positioning Diagnostic](references/prompts/01-positioning-diagnostic.md) on your current product
3. Map competitive alternatives using [the mapper](references/prompts/02-competitive-alternative-mapper.md)
4. Draft one market insight using [Insight Reverse-Engineer](references/prompts/07-insight-reverse-engineer.md)

### 7-Day Sprint
- **Day 1:** Complete positioning diagnostic + competitive alternative mapping
- **Day 2:** Build differentiated value chains for all key features
- **Day 3:** Sharpen target customer definition using the sharpener
- **Day 4:** Select market category framing
- **Day 5:** Draft full sales pitch using the architect
- **Day 6:** Build champion ammunition kit for key stakeholder objections
- **Day 7:** Test pitch with 1-2 qualified prospects and iterate

### 30-Day Integration
- **Week 1:** Complete 5-component positioning exercise
- **Week 2:** Build and refine full sales pitch using Setup → Follow-Through
- **Week 3:** Test with best sales rep, iterate on 5+ qualified prospects
- **Week 4:** Roll out to full team, align marketing messaging, build proof stack

