## The Dunford Operating Philosophy

> Your product doesn't have a "messaging problem." It has a positioning problem. Fix the context, and the messaging writes itself.

Most companies try to solve positioning by iterating on taglines. April's approach starts at the root — understanding what customers would do without you, mapping your unique capabilities to value, and choosing the market frame that makes your value obvious. The sales pitch is just the vehicle that delivers this positioning to the buyer's brain in the right order.
